Instead , agricultural and economic assistance constitute the mainstays of our diplomatic ties with these countries .
<ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Taiwanese</ENAMEX> agricultural specialists stationed in <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Burkina Faso</ENAMEX> have converted <ENAMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">1,000 hectares</ENAMEX> of desert to arable land , while <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Taiwanese</ENAMEX> specialists sent to <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Gambia</ENAMEX> have successfully transplanted tomatoes , green beans , okra , and various leafy vegetables from <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Taiwan</ENAMEX> and raised them on <ENAMEX TYPE="NORP">Gambian</ENAMEX> soil .
